\begin_layout Problem
(8.1) Les équations d'état pour un système thermodynamique sont 
\begin_inset Formula $P=aT-b(V-V_{0})$
\end_inset

 et 
\begin_inset Formula $U=\frac{b}{2}(V-V_{0})^{2}+cT$
\end_inset

 où 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 et 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 sont des constantes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\bar under
A.

\series default
\bar default
 Démontrer que ces équations sont consistantes avec les lois de la thermodynamiq
ue (qu'elles satisfont les conditions de consistance).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
First we require that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Big(\frac{\partial U}{\partial V}\Big)_{T}=T\Big(\frac{\partial P}{\partial T}\Big)_{V}-P
\]

\end_inset

Note that 
\begin_inset Formula $\Big(\frac{\partial U}{\partial V}\Big)_{T}=b(V-V_{0})$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\Big(\frac{\partial P}{\partial T}\Big)_{V}=a$
\end_inset

.
 So the right side becomes
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
T\Big(\frac{\partial P}{\partial T}\Big)_{V}-P=aT-aT+b(V-V_{0})=b(V-V_{0})=\Big(\frac{\partial U}{\partial V}\Big)_{T}
\]

\end_inset

as needed.
 Now, we calculate 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{V}$
\end_inset

 using
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
C_{V}=\Big(\frac{\partial U}{\partial T}\Big)_{V}=c=constant
\]

\end_inset

Noting that 
\begin_inset Formula $\Big(\frac{\partial C_{V}}{\partial V}\Big)_{T}=0$
\end_inset

, we want the following condition to be satisfied:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
T\Big(\frac{\partial^{2}P}{\partial T^{2}}\Big)_{V}=\Big(\frac{\partial C_{V}}{\partial V}\Big)_{T}=0
\]

\end_inset

Since 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 is a constant, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Big(\frac{\partial^{2}P}{\partial T^{2}}\Big)_{V}=0$
\end_inset

, so that condition is satisfied.
 There are no other consistency conditions for this system.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\bar under
B.

\series default
\bar default
 Trouver l'entropie du système.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We know that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Big(\frac{\partial S}{\partial T}\Big)_{V}=\frac{1}{T}\Big(\frac{\partial U}{\partial T}\Big)_{V}=\frac{c}{T}
\]

\end_inset

We also know that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Big(\frac{\partial S}{\partial V}\Big)_{T}=\frac{1}{T}\Bigg(\Big(\frac{\partial U}{\partial V}\Big)_{T}+P\Bigg)=\frac{1}{T}\Big(b(V-V_{0})+aT-b(V-V_{0})\Big)=\frac{aT}{T}=a
\]

\end_inset

Now, the entropy 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is a function 
\begin_inset Formula $S(T,V)$
\end_inset

, so
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
dS & = & \Big(\frac{\partial S}{\partial T}\Big)_{V}dT+\Big(\frac{\partial S}{\partial V}\Big)_{T}dV\\
dS & = & \frac{c}{T}dT+adV\\
S & = & c\int\frac{dT}{T}+a\int dV\\
S(T,V) & = & c\ln(T)+aV+S_{0}\quad\square
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


